import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['miles'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.75)
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['miles'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['miles'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['miles'], data['gas'])
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Gas Used (gallons)')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between miles driven and gas used?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.groupby(data['year'].dt.year)['gas'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['year'], data['gas'], color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=data['gas'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average gas usage')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Gas used (gallons)')
    plt.title('What is the average amount of gas used per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of years in the dataset?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    driving_sides = data['side'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(driving_sides, labels=driving_sides.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of driving on different sides of the road?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
